name: Smoked Taillight Tint/Headlight Vinyl BULK ROLL 24"X10 FEET! (20% Dark Smoke) FREE SHIPPING!
description:
This listing Is For 1 roll of our Dark smoke Tail light/Headlight Vinyl. The size of the roll is 24" wide by 10 feet length!

    

  About Our Vinyl
    
    * Gloss surface
   
    * Has UV stabilizers and provides UV protection for your lights.
   
    * Tail Light/Headlight Vinyl designed to be stretchy enough to be heat conformed to curved/Contour lights.

    * Can be applied to Tail Lights/Headlights, Fog lights, Side Markers, interior lights.

    * Designed to last five to seven years on your lights.

    * Step by Step install Instructions.

    * Not static cling, Window Tint, or Laminx.This Vinyl Has a special Adhesive backing.

    * Sold in widths of 24 inches
    
    * Easy to install it yourself, requires a little patience. But professional installation is recommended.

    * Can be removed with out damaging your Tail Lights and or no residue left behind.

    * Gives your car, motorcycle or truck that nice looking style.

   
 

What is needed to apply your Vinyl On My Tail Lights/Headlights?

(1.)  Xpin Vinyls recommends the use of an installation tool such as a squeegee, plastic card, or any credit card type card to help reduce the air bubbles during installation.

(2.)  A heat gun or hair dryer will also be needed to heat and stretch the vinyl when applying it to the curvy/contour edges of the headlights/tail lights.

(3.)  Using application solution such as Isopropylene Alcohol mixed with water will help remove any tar, dirt, oil or debris from the surface of your lights.

(4.) Two drops of baby shampoo in a squirt bottle full of water will help in the wet application of your installation for our vinyl.

(5.) A microfiber cloth (lint free cloth).

(6.) Hobby knife or exacto blade.

(7.) Our vinyl Film

We recommend the use of these products for great results.


What is the difference between your Tail Light Vinyl Film and The So-Called Pre-Cut Kits?

The Difference between our vinyl sheets and the pre cuts is that our universal sheets gives you more flexibility and more room to stretch the vinyl as much as needed while wrapping your lights, pre cut kits are limited to that, while some pre cut kits are sometimes not even cut right and tend to be a little off.


 Are your colored films legal on Tail Lights/Headlights for street use?
 
 Our colored vinyl may not be legal for street use on primary lighting. Please check your state or local laws before application.



About your order

All of our kits are quality checked for any flaws, defects, rips,or anything that doesn't seem normal before being shipped out. You don't need to worry about us shipping bad defected products. Our vinyl is very fresh and cut on demand when your order is placed, we do NOT sell old vinyl nor keep it stored longer than it's shelf life.
